description:
File: rust/lichen-gateway/src/slip.rs
Line: 301

The rx_buffer in SlipFramer grows without bound when receiving data. If a malicious or faulty sender transmits a continuous stream without any FEND delimiter, the buffer will grow until memory is exhausted.

Current code at line 301:
```rust
SlipDecodeResult::Byte(b) => {
    self.rx_buffer.push(b);
    None
}
```

The initial capacity is 2048 bytes (line 150), but there is no maximum limit enforced.

Impact: Denial of service via memory exhaustion. An attacker on the mesh network or a faulty serial device could cause the gateway daemon to crash.

Fix: Add a maximum buffer size constant and truncate/reset the frame when exceeded:
```rust
const RX_BUFFER_MAX: usize = 4096; // or match MTU

SlipDecodeResult::Byte(b) => {
    if self.rx_buffer.len() >= RX_BUFFER_MAX {
        // Frame too large - discard and reset
        self.rx_buffer.clear();
        self.rx_in_escape = false;
        None
    } else {
        self.rx_buffer.push(b);
        None
    }
}
```

Tags: security, memory, dos, gateway
